Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{60%grams}. Stir-fry, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Boil the @spaghetti{180%grams}, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through.

Stir the @chicken stock paste{10%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{75%milliliter} into the bacon. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Next, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%grams}, @peas{120%grams} and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}.

Add the spaghetti and toss to combine. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add a splash of water if the sauce is too thick.

Stir in the @Truffle Zest{1%sachet}, then remove from the heat.

Share the pasta between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!